The internet was thrown into chaos just this morning when a BBC documentary which was released today exposed how university lecturers sleep with students in exchange for good grades. Kiki Mordi who happens to be the investigative journalist who exposed the dirty deeds of these lecturers has been hailed by celebrities worldwide. Simi and her husband, Adekunle Gold join the plethora of celebrities that have hailed the young lady. Both artistes took to their respective Twitter pages to commend Kiki for exposing the evils that have gone down for decades in tertiary institutions. Simi wrote “Much respect to @kikimordi for this bravery. These conversations need to be had. The animals need to understand there is no hiding place. Even if the system doesn’t fight for us, ur shame will fight against you. #sexforgrades.” Adekunle Gold wrote “God bless Kiki Mordi for this #SexForGrades thing. Been wondering when someone was going to address it”. Much respect to @kikimordi for this bravery. These conversations need to be had. The animals need to understand there is no hiding place. Even if the system doesn’t fight for us, ur shame will fight against you. #sexforgrades — Simi (@SympLySimi) October 7, 2019 https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js God bless Kiki Mordi for this #SexForGrades thing. Been wondering when someone was going to address it. — AG BABY (@adekunleGOLD) October 7, 2019 https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js The post Simi & Adekunle Gold Hail BBC Journalist, Kiki Mordi For Exposing University Lecturers In New Documentary appeared first on tooXclusive. Source: Too Xclusive